column5: Finally got the boat ready for the season and decided to head out for Lakers on Simcoe.  Went 4 for 4, so a good day overall.  Kept one for the BBQ and let the rest go to be caught another day  Was quite foggy out there this morning.  Bugs were nasty.  Here's a few pics from the day.
Nice going. I think you guys were further out then us if you had fog. yes the bugs got nasty.
Nice report and beautiful photos Joey. Thanks..
nice going, we looked for you and swerved towards every lund we saw, but none were you and Tybo too
Nice fish and great conditions as well!!
Hahahaha, I wondered if you were out in the new boat and was swerving for Lund's aswell   Thanks all.  Looks like they're all natural fish too!  Nice to see
now june  15th is the delivery date
You have enough lake trout to hold ya over til then.
Give those ducks a few weeks and well, BBQ again, nice pictures.
Sure looks nice on the water.  Those fish got some size to them too.
Awesome Darlin!!!    Great angler & fish shot.  Good shootin' out there too.
Wow, thanks Drew    Thanks Ketchenany, never tried Canada goose!   Glen, the one Paul got sure had some shoulders on it!!
Fantastic fish there, guys! A great first day of the season in the boat as well. Congrats!
Simcoe, sure is a great fishery   lots of good looking greasers in this report also   Great job Joey & Paul   First time out, you guys did awesome!!! Thanks for sharing! Jacques
Glad to hear the pair of ya got out. And some decent fish to boot.... nice!   Cheers, Ron...
Well done. some nice fish and photos
Looks great. You did a lot better than me this long weekend.
